Iranian students are prepared to die for their country's nuclear program.
Formed a human shield.
Several hundred university students formed a human shield around nuclear facilities in Iran.
With his gesture want to express their support for his country's nuclear program before a possible Israeli attack.
Students came to pray on Tuesday at noon at the facilities and then chanted slogans of death to America and Israel.
Several hundred university students formed on Tuesday in the Iranian city of Isfahan human shields around the nuclear technology center in that works with uranium.
Intended to demonstrate that they are ready to defend his country's nuclear program with their own lives.
The International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA), in a recent report, noted that Iran, by all accounts, strives to obtain nuclear weapons.
Israel in talks about a possible attack on Iranian nuclear facilities.
Students came to pray at noon at nuclear facilities in Isfahan and then launched penalty slogans against the US and Israel.
In case of attack, whose goal would be to stop the Iranian nuclear programme, would be achieved, according to Israeli sources, not only the plant in Isfahan, but also the Natanz facility, which enriches uranium.
Daily menu of a child obese: Not desayuna sausages and dinner
More than a third of children aged between 9 and 13 years have problems of overweight, where the overweight affects the 9% of the school population and obesity to 5%.
Obese children are mostly from families with a lifestyle that is not healthy, according to current investigations.
Becomes to show what the importance of the environment where it grows to a healthy development of the person, as well as the models that serve as a reference.
In the table, obsessive children are, for example, of sausages at least twice as frequently as the children of families with normal weight.
For dinner, more than 19% of the obese had cenado chips on the day before the analysis, which is linked to the prevention programme "The obesity is not a coincidence."
In the families of overweight children there is no tradition of sports, which applies to most families today, where only 15% of children responded that their parents, at least once per week, found time to exercise.
Survey 900 children
The survey was conducted at the end of last school year and participated in the same almost 900 children of Basic Education throughout the Czech Republic.
It was the second edition of the programme of "The obesity is not a coincidence," which supports the General Health Insurance Company and the company Unilever.
Until now, have participated in the project more than 12,000 children from the fourth to the eighth grade.
A proper diet and exercise in family are determining factors, which are significantly reduce the number of overweight children and even obesity.
"Only half of the children polled have responded with five meals a day, according to the regime: Breakfast, lunch, dinner, tea and dinner, which is one of the basic conditions for a healthy diet," says one of the results of the survey.
Without breakfast for dinner but with sausage
Specialists warn that, in a healthy development, are important, moreover, the details, which also include, for example, have a fixed time for breakfast in the family.
In the Czech Republic, however, only 23% of families of schoolchildren eat breakfast at the same time.
In the majority of families, each desayuna alone.
But the worst was to discover that in 10% of households are not desayuna nothing.
Breakfast, however, is the basis of a daily diet.
The study shows that in the families of obese children consumed much more often unhealthy the chips.
Almost everyone - regardless of weight - drink daily sweet drinks (70%).
As a general rule make sport more than 40% of the children surveyed, however, between their parents this result is reduced to less than half, only 15%.
Diet Fabrícate your
The next phase of the study made it possible for kids elected (204 boys and girls of 13 schools) creates its own expenses from all the offers possible according to their tastes and opinions.
"Food preferences of Czech children aged between 12 and 15 years, from the point of view of a healthy diet, they are far from the ideal."
Among his favourite foods are pasta, meat and sweets
"It is especially alarming the popularity of the drinks sweet," is in the final report of the study.
As the main meal takes the biscuit pasta and closely follows the poultry meat.
Practically, children are always the pulse) and a taste for the fish and vegetables is very low.
Healthy habits change
At the same time, the study shows that children are ready to change their eating habits if they receive fair information.
"In the control group of participants in the study who completed the questionnaire after ending the prevention program" The obesity is not a coincidence, "was in many cases a major change in favour of the principles of healthy eating," noted in the results of the study.
Draws attention, for example, the sweet lemonade, where many children would start to prefer the ordinary water.
Children also choose more frequently in the questionnaire poultry meat and fish for food and would restrict the consumption of fresh food and derivatives of flour.
