Paclík also points out that, in case defeat, would remain in the office of president only until 2013, when reached the turn of ordinary general assembly.
In that role he would like to see an expert and a good manager who is not too connected with the football events.
"I have already spoken to some people who could take into account."
"For me it was crazy to hear some say that at this moment not even want to identify with the Czech football."
"I would like to change that vision," he adds.
What supposedly more upsets Paclík at this moment is Pelta's relationship with the president of the Football Association of Regional Plzeňský Roman Berbr, a man with a controversial past, known outside the little world as a powerful lobista with ability to influence the vote of delegates in the General Assembly.
