If, in the fourth General Assembly elected the current vice-president Jindrich Rajchl as the new chairman of the Football Association, many people would probably be resentful.
Rajchl promised that, if elected, he would work hard.
It wants to implement a systematic change and make that members of the executive committee are responsible for each area of football individually.
Also undertakes to resolve the case of the Bohemians, improving relations with UEFA and FIFA, get more money for football and continue with the work begun by the former president Ivan Hašek.
"As president, I would like to devote myself full football."
"From international contacts with UEFA and FIFA until the selection, via professional football or the training of young footballers of high performance."
"This is not to say that it would do everything alone," he said in an interview for Rajchl ÈTK.
"I am a team player and I want to divide the powers of the executive committee in such a way that each member can engage in a specific area."
"And asignaré difficult tasks for that football can, in each of those segments, go ahead with a lot of momentum."
"To many people that probably would not be happy, because it will begin to work very hard and not just to criticise the work of others," he added.
Due to the atmosphere of criticism in the football movement, said that he had considered the possibility of not stand again as a candidate.
"You know, that work 20 hours a day."
"But I need to know that this makes sense and that there will be people behind me and I will stop at every turn," explained the reasons for his indecision.
"A lot of people told me that I must not give up, because then they would give up others."
"It is to have faith in order not to leave as well, without more," he said.
They say, also motivates him to continue the work already started with Hašek.
"During those two years, it ended a large part of the work that I do not want now be lost."
"There are processes that had begun and that will have its effect within a couple of years and I would not like to see someone the stop," announced worried by the fact that, if you choose to another candidate, Miroslav Pelta, the situation in the partnership could return to be as it was before the era of Hašek.
"I believe in order, and that is something that, in my opinion, Mirek Pelta is not able to maintain.
"Behind him is especially all those people who would take care of football to be just a privilege for a select few."
"I can blame a lot of things, but not the fact that I am in favour of someone."
"Attempt to be objective."
"I would like to make a football for all, because only then will be well all and not just those elected," said Rajchl.
Also rejects the idea that only serious bohemio the president.
"Although some people are trying to pretend otherwise, I have in mind to do the utmost to Moravia."
"For example, it is time to think about the fact the split second division in a Czech side and another Morava, whose winners would go to the first division."
"Does not give the current situation in which we have only three teams of Moravia, which is a problem for the Moravians young players," said Rajchl.
Although the battle of the presidential elections joined Tomaš Paclík, president of the Club Pilsner, Rajchl continues to believe in his chances of being elected.
"I still have a strong support from the Czech Federation, which I chose as his vice president and who knows that there are clear successes behind me," said Rajchl, whose successes include saving tens of millions of kroner disadvantageous contracts, negotiations of television contracts and negotiations on the law of the lottery.
On the other hand, recognises their share of the blame for the federation is not united.
And while Pelta proclaims that it is "disqualified to restore confidence in the Czech football," believes the other rival, Paclík, as a strong candidate who has something to offer football.
"Nobody can deny that did a great job in the Pilsen that year."
"In the event that is elected, probably will continue to what already began Ivan Hašek exchange rate and not significantly the number of staff in the committees."
"I do not want to use that in my favour," assesses their rivals Rajchl.
Europe's most beautiful swimming pools
The blue leap
Julia Stanek for
Swimming pools from an incredible perspective, sumptuous restrooms in Budapest: Who visit Europe can live their wonderful blue, and, after a visit to the city or a walk, rest their weary legs in bathrooms bubbly.
A book shows where is the best welfare in the water.
When Iris Meder conducted a research trip during the past year and a half, there was something that could not be lacking in their luggage, a swimsuits shown.
Backs lying down on the water, looked the artistic leadership at the top, swam towards the angelotes of marble, that the expected on the edge of the pool and pool deck asombraba before the modernist meticulously restored.
I liked the bathroom, noted in his book at the time of all the interesting details about the style and the history of the building.
The architectural historian Meder explored more than 200 swimming pools in this way and presented in his recent book "Badefreuden": Swimming pools covered in Munich, the historic palaces of bathing in the Black Forest, "concrete buildings" in Taunus.
Made his "journey by the most extraordinary baths of Central Europe" by 13 countries: In addition to Germany, Austria and Switzerland, visited places of Italy, France, the Czech Republic, Slovakia, Slovenia, Hungary, Romania, Poland, and a city respectively in Luxembourg, Serbia and Croatia.
This German 46 years is a real fan of the culture of the bathroom.
Wants nothing to do with the sport, said Meder, only water is different.
Only bothers him that fans will have to settle for bath blue tiles and smell of chlorine, while fans can breathe fascinating to run the smell of forests of fir trees or listen to the cheerful trinos of birds in the park.
"One day I wondered why the swimming pools must always be so ugly," says the head of Vienna.
"I began collecting fine swimming pools."
The surface of the water double the architecture.
The chapoteo in the swimming pool and the ethereal oils of the sauna. The factor of welfare in the swimming pools is so great because it addresses all the senses, according to Meder.
And if the builder strives, covered swimming pools can be a real gift to view: "Instead of soil, in the bathrooms are covers an area of water."
"On the one hand it is transparent, on the other hand, reflects the beauty of the whole building."
All bends optically: High vaults, the tiles of colours, the launch pads.
The book with photographs in small format "Badefreuden" provides in 190 pages very interesting data on the architecture and history of art in the historic oasis of welfare, but, one might be tempted to jump to the blue.
Meder, the collector of swimming pools discovers the copies in its investigations in Hungary.
Alongside the magnificent medicinal baths as the Széchenyi of Budapest, 100 years, are the waters with nitrates in a unique kárstica cavity (baths in cavities in Miskolc-Tapolca), as well as a spa, whose swimming pools are alkaline water and are in a building with a bottle (Városi Termálfürdö in Jászberény).
Many swimming pools discovered in Switzerland and Austria offer spectacular view: While the entire city puts the eyes in the swimming pool of Zurich overhead, you can look at Arlberb, covered in snow, from the outside of a swimming pool in St. Anton, and: In the Turkish bath is a window from which you can see the practice in the ski runs.
The design, perhaps, more extraordinary expected to customers in Längenfeld: The cathedral of water Ötztal seems a ovni just land in the Alps.
Steam rises from three sources open in winter, while in the mountains of Ötztal standing up in the sky.
Alhambra in the Black Forest
At Meder, the collector of swimming pools, it was invading the smell of chlorine in all the swimming pools.
Many thermal baths smell of sulphur, in the bathrooms of Árpád in Békescsaba, Hungary, the plague on diesel is so strong that people think we have reached a health bathing.
The smell comes from medicinal waters containing bicarbonate and alkali and whose loam sticks to the skin to enter into the swimming pool, a Enjoyment welfare in a special way.
Iris Meder is also disappointed in a place in their quest for beautiful places for bathing, when he wanted to visit discovered swimming pools and baths sun bathing in the Czech Luhatschowitz, found itself with a blocked field.
The bloodbath 1902 the architect Duan Jurkovic was closed.
When Meder looked through the windows of the building abandoned modernist red, white and yellow, saw the undergrowth grow between the tiles.
Counters the decline in a lovely pool in the Black Forest: The Palace spa in Bad Wildbald.
These bathrooms have three phases of construction behind; not only can discover neorománicos elements in times of its construction in 1844, if not an Arab hall style Alhambra, added in 1900.
Since his diligent modernization in 1995, the Palace spa bath is the favorite of the collector of swimming pools, Iris Meder, and not only because it is natural for the Black Forest.
"Has a lot of merit merge different architectural styles in a unit so fantastic," says Meder.
In a palace immersion in the swimming pool and spa apparently has no great importance.
Agricultural speculation
Deutsche Bank analyzes the business of raw materials
To Christian Teevs
Does renunciation Deutsche Bank to its business with agricultural raw materials?
According to Spiegel-online, Josef Ackermann has commissioned a working group to see the consequences of speculation for the world's poor.
In January, the head of the consortium wants to show the consequences.
Hamburg,
For citizens, the matter is clear, according to a study by 84 per cent of Germans do not find it acceptable that banks speculating with agricultural commodities such as wheat and maize.
Two-thirds of respondents claim that Deutsche Bank and other credit institutions will be withdrawn from this business because intensifies the problems of the world's poorest.
This is the result of a survey commissioned by the consumer organisation Foodwatch.
The study was based on a report submitted to Foodwatch in mid-October.
The author Harald Schumann shows that betting on the global commodity exchanges are up prices, and banks are burdened with the responsibility of the global problem of hunger.
The campaign of the ombudsman is aimed in particular to Josef Ackermann, director of Deutsche Bank, although the big banks such as Goldman Sachs and Morgan Stanley are acting in a similar fashion.
Originally, betting on raw materials are thought to protect traders of swings in prices.
The main experts agree that the players have been decoupled from the offers and demands, and reap profits of the costs of the poorest.
Ackermann reacted to the criticism differently than the American competitors: Promised to review the claims and said that no business "deserves to compromise the reputation of Deutsche Bank."
According to Spiegel online, an international working group is reviewing the claims of the report of Foodwatch.
The analysis should be completed by the end of the year, then the results will be presented to the directive of Deutsche Bank, along with the recommendation of how to handle the matter.
At the end of January, the management of the bank will report of the consequences.
The end there could be a reduction in the business of raw materials, or even its total abandonment.
Ackermann is trying to fix its image.
Thilo Bode, founder of Foodwatch, welcomed the news, but reaffirmed their criticism of the financial sector: "Betting on rising food prices are particularly dramatic how ruthless the banks are currently the public welfare."
Ackermann stands as the largest banking lobbyist, especially in the obligations.
"Deutsche Bank should cancel all investments in his portfolio in the game to put in the money for stakes of food prices," said Bode.
"It does not matter if Ackermann is the subject of people suffering from hunger or the fame of Deutsche Bank."
The inspection of Ackermann is surprising at first glance, but it is clear that the head of the consortium wants to offer a perfect picture a few months before leaving his post.
Monday, Deutsche Bank wrote that the chairman of the board of directors will change something different to what had not planned on the board of directors.
With the abandonment of the controversial land speculation can improve its image.
And needs that barely interested potential losses, this will be his successor.
Two-thirds would rescind the investment in raw materials
Foodwatch struggles to keep the pressure on the manager.
So far, more than 30,000 netizens have participated in the campaign of the organisation.
On Tuesday, Bode published the survey by the Forsa Institute had asked 1,001 people on 7 and 8 November.
Barely 10 per cent considered legitimate that Deutsche Bank offered investments in the bet that food prices.
Many bank customers showed personal consequences to discover that his bank was involved in such business: According to the survey, two-thirds would rescind all investments of the money that comes from land speculation.
The 43 per cent would advise against such a bank to their acquaintances, 49 per cent would, after reflect, cancel your account and would change to another institute.
The house 21 in Vienna
Moved the flag
Ingeborg Wiensowski on
A history of architecture with ups and downs and a happy ending, the flag of the Austrian exhibition in Brussels in 1958 won prizes, was in Vienna for a museum, was empty and collapsed.
Now it reopens as home of exhibitions.
The architecture of modern postgerra passionate about, forms clear, the halls of glass, the bold curves and new construction materials, typical of thought on the technical progress, for which the Austrian flag of architect Karl Schwanzer for the exhibition of 1958 Brussels is a good example and known.
The Pabellón of Schwanzer won the Grand Prix of Architecture for his slight and floating construction of steel and glass.
The building is considered to present a milestone of the contemporary architecture.
To the well-known architect who also built the flag of Austria in the next exhibition.
With his legendary tower for four cylinders MBW more the adjacent building bulldozed in Munich, became internationally known.
Its flag, designed as a temporary building for exhibitions was lifted after the exhibition in the Schweizer Garten alongside the station south of Vienna, was amended in 1962 and opened a museum of the 20th century, was called the "house 20."
The building was appropriate but lacked the appropriate technology and space for a museum; no wall to hang art, or a good atmosphere.
Despite this was used until the contemporary art in Vienna had a new home.
The building is empty since 2001 and increasingly lapses.
Currently, the architect Adolf Krischanitz reformed the flag, now calls it "home 21" and will be used in the future as a museum of contemporary art.
Tuesday afternoon opened the Belvedere museum, which owns the house, with the first exhibition, a stroke of luck in some way.
Agnes Husslein-Arch, the new director of the Austrian Belvedere gallery since 2007, achieved a new beginning.
Husslein-Arch, doctorate in art history with a remarkable career, among other things, artistic patinadora on ice in his youth, later in ', the Guggenheim museum director and founder of the modern art museum of Salzburg, made the reforms with the insistence of politicians and protectors of monuments, provided public funds and private sponsors and established its use.
With the exception of contemporary art, are the work of the sculptor Fritz Wotruba of the foundation document -, there should be a bar and a bookshop and also built an office building.
Strict control, low budget
Krischanitz was the best choice to do so.
Not only because reformed so sensitive the secession of Joseph Olbrichs in Vienna, expanded and was awarded the contract, if not because studied with Schwanzwer at the Technical University of Vienna and the flag was for him a "important place and immense," which was "almost every weekend" exhibitions.
Knew the project and the problem of the building, which disappeared with his transfer to Vienna in exchange for use with generosity and easily.
In the current reforms there are big problems, the building was "a devorador of energy," said Krischanitz.
It changed the profile of the windows on the facade of glass, was installed an insulating glass fibre reinforced glass and replaced the glass ceiling for a special safety glass.
The thermal bridges and steel beams were strengthened or substituted and the ceilings of asbestos were rehabilitated.
Two basements were used for the new use, a panel of light declined between the house and the street provides lighting, a bridge serves to enter the building almost new, but still the flag of Schwanzer.
Remain the original external doors, the house is painted in shades old mahogany and protected against rust.
And the cinema is exactly as it was before.
And all this with a strict control on the part of the office of monuments and a low budget.
"Often had to find material that was good, cheap and also would like to the office of protection of monuments," says Krischanitz and warns of a harsh land in the basement.
Despite all the pressures, problems and reforms, the building remains flexible and light.
Flag as "that came from Brussels" has been difficult, said recently Krischanitz, a typical "casual appearance in the history of the city."
An architecture that is "always in the wrong place," and that is why I wanted to "raise awareness appropriate."
In this case the house 21 is not in the wrong place, has been planning a stroke of luck. The entirely new and planned "district of the central police station," with houses and offices, sits alongside the Schweizer Garten.
And perhaps happen another stroke of luck: The house 21 could receive a strengthening of other construction of Krischanitz, because the collector Francesca von Habsburg has bought the room of temporary art and Berlin, as you hear, negotiated with the city on a neighbour in the Schweizer Garten.
Deutsche Bahn is planning a package of crisis of winter amounting to millions
The company has devised a plan of crisis, which would prevent the unserviceability of trains in winter.
To double the number of staff.
It costs millions.
In the fight against the unserviceability and train delays caused by the winter, Deutsche Bahn has been spent on this year more than 70 million, according to a newspaper report.
The newspaper Bild "reported, citing an internal crisis plan of the group, planned investments until 2005, out of a total of around 300 million euros.
So what should be better availability of vehicles and the rail network even with a long pass.
Among other things, plans to double the internal and external employees to 16,000 jobs to remove snow from the tracks and platforms.
The aim is to clean up the snow and ice platforms for the operation and 90 percent of the needles needed for the operation at the end of four to five hours.
Two months ago, Rüdiger Grube, chairman of Deutsche Bahn, warned breakdowns and delays to trains also during this winter after a summit with the government and industry.
Last winter Deutsche Bahn suffered considerable problems in passenger transport, because, among other things, he failed reservations about adverse weather conditions.
Many regional train for years waiting for a new authorisation of the federal railway office.
There is a delay in the delivery of high-speed trains.
Deutsche Bahn has been working for years to see the axes of high-speed trains often in the workshop, after a high-speed train was the rupture of an axis in the central police station in Cologne.
Deutsche Bank pays millions in fines in the US.
After the tumult on the president Josef Ackerman, there is a new problem for the US, Deutsche Bank must pay a fine millions.
As if the problems were not enough for the Deutche Bank, its past in the US is the giant of the industry, the Institute of Frankfurt pays $145 million (106 million euros) in a deal to end the feuds due to the bankruptcy of five major credit unions during the financial crisis.
Is the sale of mortgage securities.
The regulation of financial markets NCUA criticizing many big banks induce credit unions with false promises to buy financial products; they have downplayed the risks.
Such titles lost their value during the financial crisis and lead banks to the depths.
"We are pleased to be able to clarify the issue without the parties having to go to court," said a spokesman for Deutsche Bank in New York.
The bank does not admit any fault with the agreement.
This also applies to Citigroup, which forced a payment of $20.5 million.
Debbie Matz, chairman of the NCUA, held the deference of both financial institutions.
The National Credit Union Administration (NCUA) is responsible for credit unions in the US and provides support in the event of bankruptcy to protect investments of customers.
The NCUA tries to reintegrate the losses caused millions.
The agreements are currently closed its first type.
The regulator had also asked accounts to other big banks and in summer filed lawsuits against JPMorgan Chase, the Royal Bank of Scotland and Goldman Sachs.
In the case of the dubious mortgage securities, are the so-called mortgage-backed securities.
These are based on housing loans.
When the US housing bubble burst in 2007, led to the downfall of many financial institutions.
In September 2008, at the height of the financial crisis, the US investment bank Lehman Brothers collapsed.
Although the results came a few years ago, currently a wind is blowing complicated for US banks.
Investors and inspection countless processes have begun to receive compensation or punish mistakes.
The Federal Housing Finance Agency (FHFA) has been the greatest number of demands.
Accuses the 18 major international banks that the two US state mortgage agencies Fannie Mae and Freddie Mac were seized in the business of mortgages in a volume of approximately $200 billion.
Deutsche Bank also has a demand of the FHFA, it is business for $14.2 billion dollars from 2005 to 2007.
The inspection demands that the Institute of Frankfurt responds to "substantial losses," without naming an exact figure.
Deutsche Bank rejected the debts as unfounded and explained that he wants to defend himself.
