The bank of Lake Zurich scandal
The bank more risky in Europe is not in Italy or France, if not in Switzerland.
The UBS almost went bankrupt in the financial crisis and since then slid from one crisis to the next.
Now directs a German.
Not sure that Axel Weber had thought.
After his dramatic departure from the summit of the federal bench in July was known in 2013 would start in a new and almost equally spectacular work: President of the administrative council of the great Swiss bank UBS, an unexpected and lucrative step in his career.
Axel Weber is happy publicly praised for its beauty and Switzerland's UBS for its newly acquired solidity and leaves fall kind remarks about their future colleagues.
"The USB has achieved a revitalization."
"I am happy to collaborate with Kaspar Villiger and Oswald Grübel."
In September, it became clear that everything would be entirely different.
A USB financial operator in London avoided all the bank's security systems and defrauded 1.7 billion euros.
Oswald Grübel, director-general of the USB, a banker not only known in Switzerland, had to go.
The chairman of the administrative council of USB was seen since then also touched on, and all asked: When is Axel Weber?
Weber was known to advise the bank since February 2012.
And will take over the chairmanship of the administrative council in May, not at the beginning of 2013, as the bank reported on Tuesday.
This is hard to Axel Weber.
It is not a banker, rather, economics professor and adviser and has had a period of adjustment is probably necessary.
Coup is responsible for the strategy of a bank, which has just returned to prove that deserves the title "the biggest bank of the scandal of Europe" for some time.
On the one hand, the USB is enormous, until recently, was the world's largest asset manager, and on the other hand, for years, is mired in a scandal to the next.
Nothing, it seems, he saves at once so proud Swiss bank.
Began the financial crisis.
The USB had an excellent reputation until 2007.
The image of the Swiss property manager discreet and solid, but also tricky, combined with ambitious goals, also wanted to be a large number in the investment banks.
On the one hand, with 1.6 trillion, the USB manages more money from wealthy clients than any other bank in the world.
And on the other hand, advanced as investment bank in the league of big banks in the world.
This impressive.
Hans Geiger, the former banker and subsequent professor of banking in Zurich for many years, explains: "To my students, I have always described the USB as a model of a good bank."
"From today's point of view, one wonders: How could be wrong?"
Was in a big mistake.
In 2007, it came to light that something went very wrong in the sticks.
In the middle of the year, Peter Wuffli, director general, which until then was regarded as a brilliant banker and very intelligent, surprisingly resigned.
A few months later, suspected the reason.
The fund's investment bank embarked on losses with high-risk securities and had to write off billions.
To shoulder this, the USB announced a capital injection of nothing less than 13 billion francs.
For this found investors, of course that some look with contempt until shortly before: A state fund Asian and opaque of Singapore and an Arab state fund, so discreet, which had never been heard his name.
This was only the first blow.
In April 2008, worsened.
The bank had to declare the loss of billions, Marcel Ospel, the chairman of the administrative council, in 2006 in the second-best paid administrative council of Switzerland, resigned.
In October 2008, continued the disaster, in view of its misguided investments, the UBS was found in the financial crisis facing bankruptcy and had to be rescued by the state.
The national bank bought distressed securities to the UBS by many billions, the Swiss Confederation gave six billion francs for a mandatory convertible bond, which became co-bank.
All Switzerland was affected, it said the dramatic that was this for a small country, if all such large banks.
Finally, the sum of the balance sheet of the UBS in 2007 was more than five times greater than the economic performance of Switzerland (see chart).
"We cannot go back to rescue the UBS," said Geiger, an expert in banking.
The first disaster joined the second.
A few months later, the UBS capitulated in a tax dispute with America and was ready to hand over details of wealthy clients, which may have disappointed taxes with the help of the bank.
In addition, adopted a figure of 780 billions of dollars, reimbursement of unwarranted benefits of these business with compensation for payment.
With this, the UBS confessed more or less have helped in tax fraud.
At the same time lost something that had always been its capital in the competition for wealthy clients: The glow of discretion.
After the scandal, the Swiss bank secrecy is no longer the same.
This was followed by the resignation of the chairman of the board and the president of the administrative council.
And the exodus of funds of clients.
In this way, in a few months, the bank lost its credibility in its two key areas: In the investment banking through the erroneous speculation and in the administration of goods through aid for tax fraud.
And just when he returned to be more calm, just when it was thought that the UBS returned to achieve this, it is this wretched history of the operator, an individual operator defrauded 1.7 billion euros, before the bank realised that something was wrong.
And it was unveiled, apparently, this still does not work well with the management of risk in the investment banking.
"With the case Adoboli statesing that risk controls have changed too little," says Martin Janssen, a professor of economics and finance at the Banking Institute of the University of Zurich.
The financial director of a large German bank is also sure: "The problem of the UBS is not that dominates the risk controls."
So the idea of caution, with which the Swiss bankers were submitted for some time, be the guardians of the greatest assets of the world: No risk too big, on the other hand, the safety of the money it wants to break on the other side of the Alpine republic.
Security deposits of Swiss banks were the symbol of the iron reliability, as Lindt chocolate Sprüngli and real.
The plant of the UBS in Zurich does not fit with the cliché of the strong Swiss private bank, is only a little higher.
The situation is classic.
The bank has its headquarters in the street Bahnhofstraße of Zurich, which runs from the main station directly to the lake in Zurich, surrounded by snow-covered summits of the Swiss mountains.
Here the buildings are ostentatious, rents are among the highest in Europe.
Here are smash as Tiffany's between traditional business as the Swiss confectionery Sprüngli.
Living here for years the Swiss banks: From the national bank, through the palace of Credit nothing, until the elitarios private banks as Julius Bär.
It comes into the reception room of the UBS through a heavy revolving door.
Inside the walls are lined with marble, before they are large leather chairs, along with the bank's logo is a great sign to indicate the "security".
The UBS knows what the customer wants here: Security.
The two big Swiss banks, UBS and Credit nothing, at some point have shifted the idea of the big Swiss bank, or have betrayed, as does the president of a small Swiss private bank.
Prefers not to read her name in the newspaper, after all, as all Swiss bankers, also with the business of the two big banks.
The UBS has become too big, believes, mainly in investment banking, where the Anglo-Saxons have gained ground.
The Swiss had nothing more to say.
"And have been used for a long time to the customs of the Anglo-Saxons."
Indeed, the UBS changed the Anglo-Saxon investment banking, gave his first major gain and then came the disaster, no European financial entity had lost so much money in the jungle of high risk as the big Swiss bank.
On 15 October 2008, the disaster was obvious.
"This Wednesday, the coalition government of the tiny country of seven million decided the greatest rescue operation in the history of their nation," writes the author Lukas Hässig in his book "Der UBS-Crash" ("The crash of the UBS" in Spanish).
Politicians gave up to 68 billion francs, or approximately 45 billions of euros to save the big bank of bankruptcy.
How it happens?
Talks with Swiss bankers, see the problem in the dimension of the UBS.
In June 1998, two of the three major Swiss banks merge into a powerful consortium.
There is a bank that, due to the merger, was too big for the small Switzerland, and continues to grow.
So that served for the two different banks precursors of the UBS complement: A bank rich but slept with the heart of the administration of goods in Zurich and internationalization poorer but stronger.
Suddenly, investment banks internationalized arrived in a timely manner with a lot of money, which could make a great financial bike.
There are two names associated with the rise of the UBS: Peter Wuffli, head of the Association of the UBS from 2001 to 2007, and Marcel Ospel, then president of the administrative council.
"I always thought that Wuffli Ospel and were a perfect team," says the expert on banking Hans Geiger.
"Wuffli, the intellectual, modest, that meant a lot of models and statistics, and Ospel, intuitive that managed to make headway since learning in the bank until the summit."
Finally, Ospel relied on Wuffli.
And in the end Wuffli probably made a decisive mistake: "Thought that their models were a reality," said Geiger.
"It is a tragic case."
Tragic, perhaps.
It is clear: The Nonsense came before the event.
Employees of the UBS clearly remember meetings of managers, in which Wuffli, the head of the consortium, always repeated the same slogan: Lowering the throne to Goldman Sachs.
The American bank was the most powerful investment bank in the world.
Topped the "League tables," classifications that then documented the success of the banks.
The UBS wanted to be at the summit.
Some steps he went well.
In the operations of foreign currency and in the negotiation of actions was higher.
However, the business advisers charged showed a weak point: In the business of international interest, in the language of banking "fixed income," there is a huge compensation for the big banks.
The UBS has gaps in the American mortgage products.
To fill these gaps, the UBS began an adventure that nearly cost him his life.
Eager for growth, invested so much the same bank as one of its hedge funds created American investments in high-risk.
Transformed itself into a powerful machine to securitise mortgages American and then sell them, maintaining certain risks to their own account.
And also, as other banks sought the fall for a long time.
"In the summer of 2007, as the American housing market was in flames, the UBS bought there," said Geiger, an expert in banking.
So great euphoria, so deep the fall.
A manager had to leave, because the attempt to organise turned out to be more complicated than expected.
Posts in the UBS became proyectables seats and are unsafe until today.
Currently, who heads a large bank, has an almost impossible job.
Must find a strategy for a bank, to which all the logical business models are lost.
Geiger, an expert in banks, has an idea, put an end to the investment banking, concentrate on property management, return to the Swiss roots.
The bank does not want to go so far (yet).
But the investment banking should reduce much, it is clear today.
The next Thursday, Sergio Ermotti, the new president of the bank, will present its future strategy to the world.
In reality, it was only in the Italian-Swiss 51 years as a transitional solution, because the bank the bank is surprisingly Grübel separated from his predecessor.
In the meantime, he imposed: Should conduct permanently business of UBS, told the bank in Zurich on Tuesday.
Ermotti wants to return the investment bank to its state in the mid-1990s.
Deletes 3,500 jobs.
But this is not enough.
The UBS needs a vision.
Who is?
What he wants to earn money?
These are the questions that are sure Axel Weber.
So far only said that first seek a house with his wife in Zurich.
The next year.
