Smart Grajos spread in cities
In many places the grajos are considered "birds problematic": These are not expelled inteligentísimos animals of cities for a long time, say experts.
About love, others want to get rid of them very quickly, for years the grajos belong to the image of the city, but in many municipalities accumulate complaints from neighbors in the dirt and noise of animals.
Although there has been no way against the "birds problematic" until now.
The grajos no longer out of cities, say experts in the first symposium on grajos to read, East Friesland.
There the specialists throughout the national territory argue about possible solutions.
Looking for alternatives in cities
Environmentalists attribute the problems of the cities to migration from the countryside of certain grajos protected; chemical applications in agriculture have visibly with the traditional habitat.
Hunting, the growing construction and falling trees that the guests make the lives of birds.
The grajos are protected.
There are large colonies with more than 600 reproductive partners in Soest, Westphalia, among others, in the northwest, among others in Jever, Diepholz and Achim in Bremen, as well as read.
There in 2005 jumped to the negative headlines of the press a controversial project to kill grajos en masse to the district.
Critics have described the hunting of the animals through traps for birds and murder with sticks as particularly brutal.
"And throwing ahuyentándolos of normal way achieves nothing," said Werner Klöver, 's landscape and read.
Shoot with water to the nests or throw trees tend to be unintended consequences, also says Manfred Kaiser, an expert in environment of Lahr and Baden-Württemberg.
"The animals are diverted, the large colonies of divide and distributed in other places."
Chasing them away is only conceivable as an exception in hospitals, nursing homes or schools.
"We must live with them, no longer the atrapamos."
Without the vicinity, does not solve the problem in cities, believes Wolfgang Kellner, mayor of reading.
It is possible a combination of scaring animals in residential areas and sensitive bait to return to settle elsewhere.
"Information panels instead of chainsaws' Uta Maria Jürgens, psychologist and against etnóloga advertised in order to treat animals in a completely different way:" The best thing is that we can withstand a peak in the face with aplomb. "
Jürgens cofounded in Schleswig-Holstein the circuit on the teaching of Ascheberger grajos, where signs are reporting on the lives of the intelligent birds.
Meanwhile, the project is accepted by tourists.
Jürgens also has its own opinion about the criticism by the noise of the birds: "Are all forms of communication, have a lot to say."
The intelligence and skill of these animals are legendary, the grajos not only exploit the resources for accessing bocados shale, if not producing tools to use them as resources.
Recently, etólogos of Cambridge University found in four grajos far does the intelligence of birds.
In an experiment, the birds learned quickly that they had to drop a stone on a platform in order to achieve a larva of moth.
Without much training, acknowledged with determination the size and the form it should take the stone to fall on the platform.
In a second test, the shrewd grajos had to solve a complicated problem.
The researchers placed a small bucket with a moth larva of in a vertical cylinder.
The birds could not reach their prey with the peak.
But researchers have left a piece of wire.
With the four animals were a hook, which caught the bucket in the sharp of the tube.
Three of the four grajos they did in the first attempt.
