Fujimori is boarding again for medical examinations
The former president Alberto Fujimori was detained on Tuesday in a public hospital to be assessed by the loss of muscle strength that presented in the legs, informed her family doctor.
Fujimori, 72, serving a sentence of 25 years in prison for human rights violations committed during his government (1990-2000), is suffering from various ailments, including a cancer in the language that has been operated on four times and that is kept under control.
Congressman Alejandro Aguinaga, who is his personal physician, said the Canal N television Fujimori will be evaluated for three days at the National Institute of neoplastic Diseases to determine the reason for the pain and the loss of strength of its members.
Aguinaga said that in his opinion Fujimori would be a candidate for the benefit of pardon for humanitarian reasons, however, said that he does not wish to do so because they are innocent.
It was operated on four times of cancer to the language, has a weight loss of weight of 18 kilos which have joined other diseases such as erosive severe gastritis, the quiste of the pancreas, kidney stones, high blood pressure and circulatory problems in the legs, listed the doctor.
Fujimori meets confinement since September 2007 in the National Directorate of Special Operations of the police.
In April 2009 was sentenced to 25 years in prison for the killing of 25 people at the hands of a squad of annihilation of the army that operated clandestinely in the early years of his government.
Mujica travels to Mexico to strengthen political ties
An official convoy, led by chairman uruguayo, José Mujica, and comprising several ministers and businessmen, will begin this Tuesday a visit to Mexico in order to expand trade between the two nations and deal with political issues in the region.
Mujica will meet on Wednesday with his Mexican counterpart, Felipe Calderón, highest point of an extensive agenda of meetings with political authorities, trade and a meeting with the collectivité Uruguayan resident in Mexico, according to the agenda disseminated by the Uruguayan Presidency.
The meeting between the two presidents, in the city of Guadalajara, will be "conducive to the exchange of information on what are the political issues between the two nations," according to published the Presidency of the South American country on its website.
According to local media, Mujica would seek to ensure that Calderón supports Uruguay in the incident with France emerged when the French leader Nicolas Sarkozy, included the South American country on a list of tax havens at the G20 meeting in the French city of Cannes.
In his speech, Sarkozy threatened to exclude from the international community to those countries that remain tax havens, which led to the rejection of the so-called Uruguay and in consultation with its ambassador in the European country.
Mexico since November chairing the G20, a group composed of the most powerful developed and emerging countries in the world, and has worked with the South American country, since January this year, an agreement to exchange tax information in order to avoid double taxation.
Uruguayan government has tried in recent years to speed up the implementation of agreements on the exchange of tax in order to get out of the "grey list" of the Organization for Economic Cooperation and Development (OECD), formed of countries that have not implemented all international standards of cooperation in tax matters.
On the trade front, Mexico and Uruguay have in place since 2004 a Free Trade Agreement (NAFTA) which has increased the exchange of goods between the two nations.
Bigotudo the plumber is the three dimensions with "Super Mario 3D Land"
Super Mario has fought, tireless, over 25 years to save Princess Peach from the clutches of the evil Bowser, but until now had never done in three dimensions: In "Super Mario 3D Land" will fight for the love of the girl in High technology.
The title, which comes this month to stores around the world, has been designed from the outset to seize the characteristics of the Nintendo 3DS portable console, which can play in three dimensions without the need to use glasses.
"Mario is the person who has to say how to operate the estereoscopía without glasses," asserted the official press Nintendo specialized in Spain, Omar Alvarez, during the presentation of the videogame in Madrid.
Alvarez indicated that "Super Mario 3D Land" is "the first of Nintendo videogame originally intended for that support," because until now successes as "Star Fox 64 3D" or "Zelda: Ocarine of time 3D" were adaptations of existing titles.
The spokesman for Nintendo has argued that, despite being in 3D, "Super Mario 3D Land" is a videogame "accessible" that allows us to enjoy a smooth and rapid departure.
Alvarez said that "Super Mario 3D Land" contains two games in one: The first part is "simple" to the entrapment users less clever.
Once overtaken, the most experts will be able to give a "second round" to the levels of the game, this time have greater difficulty.
In addition, users will be able to choose between a real time "D aggressive" or one that only affects the depth of the action, but it will be necessary to play in three dimensions in order to overcome the various challenges and "not to succumb to optical illusions."
This incursion of Super Mario in all three dimensions is also the return of the person to a portable console, which was not produced since 2005.
In this Nintendo videogame a wink to the followers of the saga and repeated the formula for success of previous deliveries, whereby the Moustache plumber will have to go mined platforms of dangers with the aim of freeing the princess Peach.
Although the player will find new movements, settings, the costume and enemies, and also a Luigi "jugable."
Colom endorses Portillo's extradition to the United States
President Alvaro Colom announced this Tuesday that gave trámite to the extradition of exgobernante Alfonso Portillo to respond in the United States for conspiracy to laundering $70 million.
That ends the process for Guatemala responded to the request from the country in the north that claimed to Portillo to judge there.
In a press conference, Colom said that its decision is due to the independence of judicial and executive powers, taking into account that a court ruling had already ordered the extradition.
He asserted that during his mandate "not got their hands" in judgments and gave all the extradition procedure that has known.
In addition to Portillo be extradited Sergio Ruano Marroquín, for murder and grievous bodily harm, and Edgar Estrada Morales and Victor Estrada Paredes, both for drug trafficking.
Done by Colom is a trámite executive after exhausting all the constitutional and judicial authorities to prosecute the exmandatario between 2000 and 2004.
In accordance with resolutions of the fifth Criminal Court and the Court of Constitutionality (CC), Portillo be extradited once it has settled their legal situation in Guatemala and guarantee their human rights.
Portillo was acquitted of embezzlement of Q120 million in the Ministry of Defense when he was president, which was the process that predated the extradition, but the prosecution appealed and revived the case.
