The body was born in order to avoid the fall in the margins of boys without training
The results of the first 25 years of life of the entity Trinijove social support is important: 6,000 young people at risk of exclusion have received aid to overcome a difficult situation throughout this quarter of a century.
Airports are over 100 jobs made today for this social group.
The anniversary served yesterday to take stock at an event held in the old manufacturing complex of Fabra i Coats attended by more than 300 people.
Trinijove was born in the district of Trinitat Vella in 1986 with the aim of helping young people with little training, without work, with problems of dogradicción or fall in the margins.
The celebration of yesterday in Sant Andreu focused to a large number of responsible for bodies and institutions that in these 25 years have collaborated with the association.
The varied political representation, in full election time, showed the unitary character of the work done by Trinijove.
Along with the president of the Generalitat, Artur Mas, and his predecessor Jordi Pujol, the event was attended by the Education exconseller socialist, Ernest Maragall, and the current mayor and councillor exteniente ecosocialista Gomà Ricard.
