The president put Trinijove as an example as to fight the bad circumstances and to give hope to people with difficulties.
"The crisis is not something new to the body and for the work it does," he said.
Vacated a farm where they were macrofiestas okupada
The invaders had grabbed 11 of the 13 floors of the building, Balmes, 51
The 12 occupants left the farm midday yesterday without offering resistance
Everything seems to indicate that the nightmare that lived the neighbours of 51 of the street of Balmes has come to an end.
Twelve people left the building voluntarily midday yesterday that were illegally, and where organised macrofiestas desesperaban that the neighborhood, by court order and without the need of a police intervention.
Ended when the operation, it changed the lock on the door to avoid a repeat of the situation.
"From now on there will be a control of access," said the manager.
The okupas, who had invaded 11 of the 13 floors of the building - the rest are habitados, were all part of the electrical and water, in addition to paint the walls and leave residues of all kinds, especially cans of alcoholic beverages.
The first three floors were the scene of mass celebrations, lasting up to two days and desesperaban tenants.
On the side of the building is a discotheque, Balmes 51, which also has been damaged.
Its owner, Maria Pantinat explained to Europe Press that since the building was occupied the business has fallen by 80%.
The owner of the discotheque notes that the invaders from the farm is unfair competition, which sold the canopy to three euros, while in the discotheque worth 10.
In addition, the owner of the local leisure had had to respond to neighborhood complaints about noise, while, as noted, not the cause inconvenience customers of the disco, but the inhabitants of the house okupada and, above all, those attending the celebrations organised there, which had increased their frequency and intensity in recent weeks, according to the angry neighbors in the area.
The head of the disco explained that the inconvenience were so large that even came to an agreement with the owner of the property and nine months ago that "forgiven" rent.
The Urban Guard also confirmed that over the last few weeks had received more complaints from neighbors about the situation.
The Chairman of the group of the PP in the municipal council, Alberto Fernández Díaz, had claimed last week "immediately vacate the property to deal with the problems of coexistence and civility that produce the neighbours, as well as the degradation of the area."
The popular leader explained that before the summer there was only one floor of the building occupied, but over the past few months the okupas had gone entering all the floors of the building and in almost all the flats, and some even have been thefts.
In this sense, he added that "it is necessary to end impunity and be strong against the incivility that has been generated in the farm."
Also yesterday, the Mossos cleared a building in Nou Barris.
At 3.30 p.m. the police turned up to 35 of the streets of Mont-RALs, after receiving a call from a neighbor who had noticed that four people came to the building.
The four were arrested at the time.
Does or mountain Park?
The architects coincide with the opportunity of the convening beyond polemics on fees
The municipal contest on the 16 door reopens the debate about the role of Collserola in Barcelona
Amediados of the 1980s, at the height of the now defunct Barcelona Metropolitan Corporation (CMB), this Administration printed Ones tracts of promoting Collserola.
The leaflet defined the mountain as the great metropolitan park of the Barcelona.
Is more, was accompanied by a comparison, in figures, with the Central Park New Yorker.
With the death of the CMB, in 1987, the park was placed in the imaginary of many, as the upper limit of Barcelona, the Catalan capital of the few that are not based in the north-south axis but above (mountain) abajo (sea).
Collserola rating as a natural park is in this idea.
The reference was no longer Central Park but Yellowstone, with the jabalís in the role of Yogi Bear.
In these was until, in September, the council convened a megacompetición composed of 16 competitions for so many other doors to Collserola.
A door refers to the idea of park, without doubt.
Either that or someone seeks to put doors to the countryside.
The question goes alone: Collserola, or mountain park?
The competition, both for his side purely organisational and by what means of reflection on the city is the topic of conversation among all the people of Barcelona architects.
It is almost as a recurring theme to fall back on when two members of this ancient caste of elected are recognized in an elevator.
And this gives rise, precisely, one of the few similarities between what they believe three architects people of Barcelona, and university teachers, which have been tabled.
Miguel Roldán, Daniel Mòdol and Marta Bayona: The contest is timely.
For Roldán, having dealt with the coastline, "it is necessary to" discuss "the face of the mountains," given that the speech Ildefons Cerdà, green apples, has not been carried out.
"It is assumed that the park more extensive Barcelona is the beach.
Among other things for his great accessibility.
Collserola is more complex, "ruling the architect for whom the title of" gates of Collserola "contains a" trap léxica ": We must not think about them" as the entrance to a park, but the demarcation of areas where we need to act. "
Mòdol, as Roldán and Bayonne with experience in the urban world, described the proposal "intellectual challenge" with "some dangers."
Dangers of "uncertain that is now projecting the public space" after the experience in the 1980s, and that was in the area of the Fòrum "his swan song."
The first fear is the demarcation of borders on where they can build.
"Limit is set for the next step," i.e., exceeding.
"We need to think in new planning tools, planning, because the current [in reference to the Metropolitan General Plan (PGM)] can lead to real disasters."
More confined himself to the question, Mòdol believes that, simplifying the Collserola vallesana aspect of "can be understood as a park, the Barcelona, not", by a matter purely topographic.
Mòdol reminds us that there is already a work done by the Collserola Patronat of that "must not fall on deaf ears," though he was grateful for the opportunity that the City offers his body to intervene in this project, "from the first moment."
And even more, understands that the closeness of the mountain with the city is the pass that allows the architects to enter the debate, but "doubt" about whether this is a technical profile that must lead the multidisciplinary teams ("a success story," said) that have had to create: "The architects should be only a tool."
Bayonne insinuated that the answer to the question that gives title to this piece is complex, because in the foundations of the tender lack a global vision of Collserola: "There have been 16 revaluing transversal competitions in the mountain-sea, but there is no longitudinal reading, watching and understands the area as a whole."
This causes, at least in his case, which has chosen to participate in the 16 contests.
In other words, a project for one of the doors may clash in programme and definition of the architect of the next door.
In his opinion, that yes, the council should ensure that the strip immediately superior to the Round of Dalt should provide, in its entirety, an area of equipment to make a smooth transition between the city and the green.
