The Secretary Dionisio Pérez Jácome gives details of the crash that killed the secretary of the Interior, Francisco Blake, and seven more people
The Ministry of Communications and Transport (SCT) reported that the results on the accident which killed the secretary of the Interior, Francisco Blake Mora and seven others, indicate that the helicopter was hit directly on the ground in complete structural integrity, without which the pilot could try a hard landing.
During a press conference, Dionisio Perez Jácome, Minister of Communications and Transport, said that before taking off the plane, the pilot found that weather conditions were right to fly.
"The elements that seem to indicate that the unit had several contacts with the ground, the aspas had contact with trees to 25 metres where the unit lost the fuselage."
Also reported that the unit was designed to 19 people, so we had the requirements needed to transport staff.
In addition, said that the inquiries made in the area of impact is not brings the emergence of pieces on the ground.
"In a search reported that there is no parts or components of the ship in another place, the impact was presented in a structural.
"The design of the helicopter was for 19 passengers, had subpoenaed suitable for shipped to passengers.
The ground presents a pending seven degrees to the 30 degrees of bias.
For the moment, the secretary assured that it is a priority to have the results before possible; however, the investigation could take several months, even a year could reach.
For its part, Gilberto Lopez Meyer, director-general of Airports and Related Services, asserted that at the moment of impact, the Chiefs of the Presidential helicopter operated in cruising speed and that this happened in a soft ground upward.
"This information strengthens the assumption of a normal cruising at the moment of impact," he said.
At the press conference, the holder of the SCT, Pérez Jácome, listed six relevant element in the research:
Visual flight:
Under the aviation regulations the flight was conducted under visual flight rules, this means that the crew must have visibility during the flight and the ground.
Weather conditions:
The reports in the AICM located right conditions at takeoff, the aircraft is moving towards the border area between the DF and the state of Mexico layers of cloud cover at low altitudes.
Selected routes:
It is likely that the cloud the crew has sought an area of lower elevation and greater visibility into the valley of Cuernavaca.
Location the impact.
The coordinates of impact and the last recording of the aircraft radar coincide, probably before the impact there was no loss of control or alteration in the flight path.
Dispersal of remains of the aircraft in a small area:
The information available so far suggest that the impact occurred in a straight path and hand.
The pattern of dispersal of remains of the aircraft may assume that the helicopter was hit on the ground in terms of structural integrity.
Has not been detected evidence of fire or explosion:
At the site of the incident are still not be disclosed evidence in the remains of the ship of some kind of explosion or fire.
Recent research results indicate that could have had multiple contacts with the ground.
During the work of countryside have been found pieces of the aircraft to an increase of 9,000,200 feet above mean sea level, the ground is a slippery from the seven degrees until 30 degrees of bias.
The photographs show the sequence in which is expected to be disbanded along this route.
The information provides elements that seem to indicate that the helicopter may have had multiple impacts on the ground.
After a thorough search in a wider area cordoned off the site, around the accident, have not been found scattered pieces of the aircraft, which strengthens the presumption that the impact was presented in conditions of structural integrity.
MSS announces protocol to find obesity gene
The Social Insurance an investigation to discover the gene of obesity in children and young people; it is supported by specialists from the negative tendencies towards
The Mexican Social Security Institute (IMSS) announced that conducts an investigation to discover the gene of obesity in children and young people, so-called protocol "Temptation of obesity in children and adolescents', which will count with markers associated with overweight.
In a statement, the head of the Medical Research Unit in biochemistry of Medical Hospital Medical Center of the National 21st Century, Miguel Cruz López, explained that incorporated a multidisciplinary team of doctors, nurses, social workers and nutriólogos.
The team is supported by specialists and postgraduate students from the National Institute of Public Health and the Center for Research and Advanced Studies (Cinvestav) of the National Polytechnic Institute (negative tendencies towards).
In research to be invited to participate in the beneficiary population or not, go to sports units of IMSS participants in the Valley of Mexico, which carried out the tests to minors, every Saturday from 8:00 a.m.
Stressed that the protocol began in Unity State of Mexico Sports Cuauhtémoc (west) and that since 8 October, the activity takes place in the Sports Unit (State of Mexico Middle).
Once it complies with the aim of bringing 500 or 600 children, the study will continue in the Sports Unit Independence Federal District (south) and finally in the Morelos Sports Unit (north of the Federal District).
He explained that the purpose of this research is to know the components and the importance of genetics with regard to the development of obesity in children and young people and identify Mexicans risk factors to prevent the emergence of chronic degenerative diseases.
To be held this November 14 World Diabetes Day, saying that the aim is to bring together three thousand children and young people between six and 14 years of age, with the consent and supervision of their parents, for the implementation of specific questionnaires on food.
Also asked about physical activity and background heredofamiliares of diseases, with the aim of avoiding risk factors that would trigger ailments such as diabetes or kidney failure.
Detailed that Saturdays are applied to all participants anthropometrics (weight, height, waist circumference of), the taking of blood pressure, blood glucose levels, triglycerides, cholesterol and insulin and genetic (it seeks to identify genes that are associated with child obesity).
Cruz Lopez noted that this research is due to the concern of health professionals for the alarming weight gain in children.
"Health surveys of 1999 and 2006 pointed out that in just six years, there was an increase in the case of children, 77 per cent in obesity, and girls of 47 per cent; in terms of overweight is also observed a dramatic rise ', highlighted the IMSS specialist.
Indicated that the justification for the search of the markers is based on the country's population differs from other genetic history.
Reported that on average, the Mexican has 65 percent of American Indian heritage, 30 percent in Europe and five percent African and this condition is reflected in the genes that are associated with diabetes and excess weight.
He explained that in general, the genetics of obesity translates into the inability to burn excess energy we consume (calories) and that is stored in the form of fat.
The researcher explained that the direct benefit for participants is the comprehensive assessment of children, which makes it possible to detect if they have some degree of overweight or obesity.
Indeed, he said, the presence of folds of dark color (acantosis) in neck and forearm, indicating the likelihood that suffer metabolic disorders and even prediabetes.
The information is handled confidentially, doctors delivered by writing to the parents, who are explains each of the measurements and changes in lifestyle that must be done to prevent disease.
Cruz López explained that there are three main components that cause overweight, obesity and other chronic ailments: Sedentarism, which is the lack of daily physical activity, remain the largest part of the day sitting in front of the television and use means of transport rather than walk short distances.
It is also due to the high caloric intake, i.e., the increased consumption of sugary drinks, carbohydrates (tamales, bread, pizza, hamburger, etc.) with high in fats and proteins and genetic analyses in this protocol.
UNAM would avoid bumpy asphalt
Rafael Herrera, researcher of the Chemistry Faculty of UNAM, develops asfaltos modified with polymers to produce a mixture with better performance, regardless of environmental conditions and temperature
If the signals it sends the pavement were met, it would not be necessary to repair potholes around 200,000 every rainy season in the Metropolitan Area of the Valley of Mexico, warned Rafael Herrera Nájera, researcher of the Faculty of Chemistry (FQ) of the UNAM, who assured that if the process of construction and maintenance of an asphalt pavement is the right one, the potholes could be reduced in number, or even be eliminated entirely.
In his conference A view of the technological potholes, handed down in the framework of the International Year of Chemistry, reported that the laboratory to office develops asfaltos modified with polymers to produce a mixture with characteristics similar to those of the asphalt, but with greater resistance mechanics, both high and low temperatures.
Herrera Nájera estimated that this kind of asfaltos modified could be used in places where the climate is extremely hot, as some cities in the north of the country, to improve their performance and, therefore, the formation of potholes.
He explained that the asphalt, the most heavy oil, is a set of hydrocarbon molecules, a high molecular weight, called asfaltenos, and other low molecular weight, called maltenos, which together give him to the pavement viscoelástico his characteristic behavior.
Asphalt viscoelástico behavior is that to high temperatures, near the 180 degrees, behaves like a liquid, to 120 degrees centigrade its viscosity is very high and 50 degrees centigrade presents an almost solid state, while at very low temperatures, the asphalt becomes brittle, he added.
This means that in the streets the resistance of the asphalt is not uniform, but which will be amended during the day in accordance with environmental conditions and temperature, warned the specialist in chemical engineering.
The investigator of the FQ noted that the streets of Mexico City mostly covered by pavement flexible, which consists of six layers of materials, of which the last three involve the asphalt.
Among the surface layers is the tar, composed of small stones covered in asphalt and then compacted.
Each piedritas that constitutes the kit, pointed out, is awash with asphalt.
The transit vehicles and generated efforts, it allows the forces are spread very well on the pavement.
If it were modified asphalt would be disseminated even better, felt the chemical engineer.
File on the tar, elaborated, it puts a final layer called rolling file, which is made of a material fine stone, i.e., a sand also washes in asphalt.
As it is the layer that is going to be in contact with the tyres of vehicles, must have more force than the tar file mechanics and provide friction along the way.
To be part of the pavement that is to receive and disseminate the efforts, the rolling file requires, we also have the proper thickness and must take care of the material from which it is made.
Climate, especially the humidity and temperature variations, are also a very important factor to consider, especially water, he said, because significantly affects the performance of the tar file.
When the ground is wets, water spreads in the interior of the kit and it is difficult to leave, this causes a reblandecimiento of all sections of the pavement and, therefore, the formation of potholes.
In the process of formation of a bump, he said, the first to become blunt is the film and only after rolling it affects the tar file, but the damage is not instantly, but that is a process that should be given to the first signs with proper maintenance programs.
Also a member of the National System of Investigadores explained that the vehicle burden is another important factor in the formation of potholes and, therefore, the thickness of each of the layers of the pavement must always be used in connection with the burden and to ensure that it meets, to avoid potholes are frequently.
Rafael Herrera warned that there is still much to investigate and work on the asphalt, for example, the tar emulsions, which in other countries are already in the market and to repair the cracks easily and without the need to use high temperatures.
